## Peptide Sequencing from an Ideal Spectrum

#This implementation reconstructs a peptide from its ideal mass spectrum using a spectrum graph approach.
#The algorithm:
#Uses an integer amino acid mass table.
#Builds a spectrum graph where each mass represents a node.
#Adds an edge between two masses  when their difference matches an amino acid mass.
#Finds all possible paths from zero to the parent mass.
#Converts each path into a candidate peptide sequence.
#Computes the ideal spectrum of each candidate.
#Returns the peptide whose ideal spectrum exactly matches the input spectrum.

  






